18:38.393 --> 18:40.307
Wow, hi.

18:40.375 --> 18:42.475
I'm guessing things went well
at the branding agency?

18:42.544 --> 18:44.024
They came up with a name for us.

18:44.150 --> 18:45.594
They said it was a sure thing

18:45.672 --> 18:47.981
that tested well from Maine to Spain,

18:48.083 --> 18:49.115
and I'm not using it.

18:49.217 --> 18:50.583
Wait, you're not?

18:50.652 --> 18:51.885
I-I'm so confused.

18:51.954 --> 18:52.979
I just had

18:53.050 --> 18:55.221
the most incredible conversation
with your mother.

18:55.324 --> 18:56.957
Okay, now I'm <i> really</i> confused.

18:57.025 --> 18:59.559
She told me this awesome story
from her childhood,

18:59.661 --> 19:01.294
and it just made me realize...

19:01.363 --> 19:03.029
we're not "sure thing" people.

19:03.098 --> 19:04.998
That's not us.

19:05.100 --> 19:06.535
You know, my old job was a sure thing,

19:06.580 --> 19:07.691
and I hated it.

19:07.754 --> 19:10.937
And... And I'll bet you handsome
Dr. Sandeep was a sure thing,

19:11.039 --> 19:13.506
and yet you chose a dreamer
with large features.

19:14.543 --> 19:18.092
Babe, we follow our hearts

19:18.117 --> 19:19.813
and we embrace the unknown.

19:20.523 --> 19:23.257
And sometimes, it is so scary.

19:23.304 --> 19:24.217
But it's also...

19:24.319 --> 19:26.586
Where all the best stuff happens.

19:26.688 --> 19:28.288
She told you about <i> ajana.</i>

19:28.390 --> 19:29.255
♪

19:29.358 --> 19:31.758
That's it.

19:31.860 --> 19:32.859
What's what?

19:32.961 --> 19:35.068
That's the name of our company...

19:35.176 --> 19:37.605
Ajana, the unknown.

19:37.964 --> 19:39.802
It's perfect!

19:39.880 --> 19:41.234
So much better than TURD.

19:41.336 --> 19:43.737
I have to do something amazing
for your mother.

19:43.839 --> 19:45.505
Don't worry,
I won't do anything too crazy.

19:45.607 --> 19:48.108
Actually, I think
I know something she'd like

19:48.210 --> 19:49.642
that <i> is</i> a little crazy.

19:49.745 --> 19:53.313
[Indian music plays]

19:54.349 --> 19:55.982
♪ One, two ♪

19:56.084 --> 19:58.339
♪ One, two, three, go ♪

19:58.441 --> 20:02.122
["Raspberry Beret" plays]

20:04.860 --> 20:10.030
♪ She wore a raspberry beret ♪

20:10.132 --> 20:14.234
♪ The kind you find
in a second-hand store ♪

20:14.336 --> 20:17.904
♪ Raspberry beret ♪

20:18.006 --> 20:22.075
♪ And if it was warm,
she wouldn't wear much more ♪

20:22.177 --> 20:24.713
♪ Raspberry beret ♪

20:27.886 --> 20:29.565
Ajana.

20:29.643 --> 20:31.922
Is it me, or does that sound
a little like vag...

20:31.993 --> 20:34.357
Do you really want to go down
that road again?

20:34.460 --> 20:36.359
- Love the name, boss!
- Me, too.

20:36.462 --> 20:38.328
But I can't take all the credit.

20:38.430 --> 20:39.329
♪

20:39.431 --> 20:40.597
[Laughs]

20:40.699 --> 20:43.500
Oh, you bastards messed
with the wrong Bengali!

20:43.602 --> 20:45.769
Oh, what's this?

20:45.871 --> 20:47.471
I'm flying!

20:47.573 --> 20:49.739
Alex, I can fly!

20:49.842 --> 20:51.808
Um, you said she was just
gonna be a minute.

20:51.910 --> 20:53.243
I got a bunch of work to do.

20:53.345 --> 20:54.945
I have never seen that woman smile,

20:55.047 --> 20:56.913
so you might wanna
get comfortable, Orson.

